        .text-center
          a#notiremind
          h2 Notifications & Reminders
        p.lead.m32 Workflow of each process is known to everyone who has access to your companies Symphony profile. This enables one to check when there is bottleneck and to rectify it. At the same time, Symphony will automatically send an email to notify and prompt the relevant person to finish his/her task thus allowing processes to flow more efficiently. On your symphony dashboard, there will be reminders on outstanding tasks left to do as well as reminders that are sent to your email.
        p.lead.m32 Workflow process is listed out to enable a clear understanding for those involved to follow the process:
        .image-title.outer-title
          .text-center
            img alt="Symphony timesheet process" width="600px" height="" src=image_path("Timesheet-process-symphony.png")
        p.lead.m32.pb32
        p.lead.m32.pb32 Outstanding tasks that will be on your Symphony dashboard:
        .image-title.outer-title
          .text-center
            img alt="Outstanding task in symphony dashboard" width="600px" height="350px" src=image_path("Outstanding-tasks-symphony.png")
        p.lead.m32.pb32
        p.lead.m32.pb32 Reminders of work pending in Symphony will be sent to your email:
        .image-title.outer-title
          .text-center
            img alt="Reminder email" width="750px" height="" src=image_path("email.jpg")



hr/

section
  .row
    .container
      .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2.col-sm-12
        .text-center
          a#WflowFp
          h2.mb64 Workflow Footprint
        .text-left
          .image-title.outer-title
          .text-left
            img alt="Workflow Footprint" width="250px" height="480px" style="float:right" src=image_path("workflow-footprint-symphony.png")
          p.lead.m32.pb32 Footprint of workflow is recorded with the username, the time stamp when action was done as well as the action that was carried out. This allows for management to track back if any errors were made in an action to rectify the problem.
          p.lead.m32.pb32 At the same time, when there are bottlenecks in workflow and workflow is held up at a certain part, management is able to check the activity log to see which action is causing the delays and also who is responsible for completing the activity. This enables a course of action that can be taken instead of being kept in the unknown about the work that is backlogged.


hr/
